        {
            "commit_hash": "9a79ac952603300ee3e8f03e77c2149989401bc8",
            "author": "Victor Hugo Borja",
            "message": "user configurable pre-post command hooks\n\nSuppose a `foo` plugin is installed and provides a `bar` executable.\nThe following hooks will be executed when set in `.asdfrc`:\n\n```shell\npost_asdf_install_foo = echo installed foo version ${1}\npost_asdf_reshim_foo = echo reshimmed foo version ${1}\n\npre_foo_bar = echo about to execute command bar from foo with args: ${@}\npost_foo_bar = echo just executed command bar from foo with args: ${@}\n```",
            "commit_url": "https://github.com/asdf-vm/asdf/commit/9a79ac952603300ee3e8f03e77c2149989401bc8",
            "removed_lines": [
                "-  result=$(grep -E \"^\\\\s*$key\\\\s*=\\\\s*\" \"$config_path\" | head | awk -F '=' '{print $2}' | sed -e 's/^[[:space:]]*//' -e 's/[[:space:]]*$//')"
            ],
            "added_lines": [
                "+  result=$(grep -E \"^\\\\s*$key\\\\s*=\" \"$config_path\" | awk -F '=' '{ gsub(/ /, \"\", $2); print $2 }')"
            ]
        },
